                :time (i / initial~4)))

            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (g2 / government-organization~8
                :name (n2 / name~8
                    :op1 "House"~8))
            :ARG2 (s2 / speaker~9))
        :manner (v / vote-01~12
            :ARG2 (m2 / majority~11)))
    :snt2 (c2 / confront-01~16
        :ARG0 (h2 / he~14
            :same-as p)
        :ARG1 (c / challenge-01~20
            :ARG0 h2
            :ARG1-of (m / major-02~19)
            :ARG2 (a / avoid-01~22
                :ARG0 h2
                :ARG1 (s / shut-down-05~25
                    :ARG1 (g3 / government-organization~24
                        :ARG0-of (g / govern-01~24)))
                :time (b / by~26
                    :op1 (d / date-entity~27
                        :day 17~27

            :ord (o / ordinal-entity~18
                :quant 1~18))
        :time (n3 / now~15)))

                    :ARG2 (c3 / country~21
                        :name (n3 / name~21
                            :op1 "Dominican"~21))
                    :ARG2 (p2 / person~23
                        :mod c3))))
        :time (a / after~20
            :op1 w)))

# ::tok Walking in circles is great when following open - access trails through villages , forests , and fields , starting and ending at the same train station .
(g / great~4
    :domain (w / walk-01~0
        :ARG1-of (s2 / start-01~19
            :location (s3 / station~26
                :ARG1-of (s / same-01~24)
                :mod (t2 / train~25)))
        :manner (c / circle-01~2))
    :time (f2 / follow-02~6
        :ARG1 (t / trail~10
            :ARG1-of (a / access-01~9
                :ARG1-of (o / open-06~7))
            :path (a2 / and~16
                :ARG1-of (e / end-01~21
                    :location s3)
                :op1 (v / village~12)
                :op2 (f3 / forest~14)
                :op3 (f / field~17)))))
